[[tab Characters]]
[[div style="border:solid 1px #999999; background-color: #f7f3e8; padding:13px; margin-bottom: 15px; font-family: 'Courier Prime';"]]
**Taskforce Ruby Lockbox:** Representatives of AOI members sent to the Pacific Theater to disrupt occult Japanese operations in the region. The squad is to use any means necessary to destroy, obfuscate, or otherwise hinder the IJAMEA war effort. 
* **Kiran Pal:** The protagonist of the series. A corporal of the Fourth Gorkha Rifles in the British Indian Army, his former platoon slaughtered in [[[walkin-slow|Don't Go Walking Slow]]], press-ganged into the secret war. He is bound to an ancient //kukri// that houses a chained protective spirit, Pramaada. 
* **Ingmar Alstrand:** Member of the Universalist Order of the Æsir. Skilled in divination and reading the will of the gods, though it has warped their mind slightly. Useful for planning assaults and avoiding ambushes.
* **Santo de Trieste:** Gormogon extraordinaire. Linguist and demolitions expert. 
* **Jacob Matthews:** Member of the Pentagram, which at this point is still involved in the Allied Occult Initiative. Good with guns and a few other things.
* **Rebekah  Ainsley:** Member of the Reformed Templars, armed with faith and steel. Consecrator of the unholy and boxing heavyweight champion. 
* **DC al Fine:** Leader of Taskforce Ruby Lockbox. Her real name is unknown, her real face is unknown. No one knows her past or her affiliations. The only certainty is her unwavering loyalty to the AOI.
